abstract: The head of Italy's central bank rebuffed criticism of its role in supervising struggling lender Banca Popolare di Bari and said in an interview published on Monday that it was ready to account for its actions.
snippet: The head of Italy's central bank rebuffed criticism of its role in supervising struggling lender Banca Popolare di Bari and said in an interview published on Monday that it was ready to account for its actions.
lead_paragraph: MILAN — The head of Italy's central bank rebuffed criticism of its role in supervising struggling lender Banca Popolare di Bari and said in an interview published on Monday that it was ready to account for its actions.
headline_main: Bank of Italy Chief Defends Regulator's Role in Bari Bank Crisis
headline_print_headline: Bank of Italy Chief Defends Regulator's Role in Bari Bank Crisis

abstract: Kyle Lowry scored 20 of his 32 points in the fourth quarter and added 10 assists and eight rebounds as the Toronto Raptors overcame a 30-point third-quarter deficit to post a 110-107 victory over the visiting Dallas Mavericks on Sunday.
snippet: Kyle Lowry scored 20 of his 32 points in the fourth quarter and added 10 assists and eight rebounds as the Toronto Raptors overcame a 30-point third-quarter deficit to post a 110-107 victory over the visiting Dallas Mavericks on Sunday.
lead_paragraph: Kyle Lowry scored 20 of his 32 points in the fourth quarter and added 10 assists and eight rebounds as the Toronto Raptors overcame a 30-point third-quarter deficit to post a 110-107 victory over the visiting Dallas Mavericks on Sunday.
headline_main: NBA Roundup: Raptors Stun Mavs With 30-Point Comeback
headline_print_headline: NBA Roundup: Raptors Stun Mavs With 30-Point Comeback

abstract: Elephants dressed as Santa Claus gave out presents and candy to students in Thailand in an annual Christmas tradition in the mostly Buddhist country.
snippet: Elephants dressed as Santa Claus gave out presents and candy to students in Thailand in an annual Christmas tradition in the mostly Buddhist country.
lead_paragraph: AYUTTHAYA, Thailand — Elephants dressed as Santa Claus gave out presents and candy to students in Thailand in an annual Christmas tradition in the mostly Buddhist country.
headline_main: Elephant Santas Deliver Christmas Presents at Thai School
headline_print_headline: Elephant Santas Deliver Christmas Presents at Thai School

abstract: Under a government regulation, teachers at some international schools face intrusive questions aimed at identifying those with “abnormal” sexual orientations.
snippet: Under a government regulation, teachers at some international schools face intrusive questions aimed at identifying those with “abnormal” sexual orientations.
lead_paragraph: JAKARTA, Indonesia — Agree or disagree, the exam asked: “I would feel uncomfortable knowing my daughter’s or son’s teacher was homosexual.”

abstract: Rugby league star and former All Blacks back Sonny Bill Williams has followed the lead of Arsenal soccer player Mesut Ozil and issued a message of support for China's ethnic minority Uighur Muslim community.
snippet: Rugby league star and former All Blacks back Sonny Bill Williams has followed the lead of Arsenal soccer player Mesut Ozil and issued a message of support for China's ethnic minority Uighur Muslim community.
lead_paragraph: WELLINGTON — Rugby league star and former All Blacks back Sonny Bill Williams has followed the lead of Arsenal soccer player Mesut Ozil and issued a message of support for China's ethnic minority Uighur Muslim community.
headline_main: Former All Blacks Player Williams Tweets Support of Uighurs
headline_print_headline: Former All Blacks Player Williams Tweets Support of Uighurs

abstract: Chinese President Xi Jinping told South Korean President Moon Jae-in on Monday that China supports South Korea's efforts to improve ties with North Korea and inject new impetus into promoting peace talks, state television reported.
snippet: Chinese President Xi Jinping told South Korean President Moon Jae-in on Monday that China supports South Korea's efforts to improve ties with North Korea and inject new impetus into promoting peace talks, state television reported.
lead_paragraph: BEIJING — Chinese President Xi Jinping told South Korean President Moon Jae-in on Monday that China supports South Korea's efforts to improve ties with North Korea and inject new impetus into promoting peace talks, state television reported.
headline_main: China Says Supports South Korea's Efforts to Improve Ties With North Korea
headline_print_headline: China Says Supports South Korea's Efforts to Improve Ties With North Korea

abstract: It was oppressively hot, above 40 Celsius (104 Fahrenheit), and the wind was picking up. Bushfires were devastating nearby towns and now threatened Yanderra, a small village with just over 600 people located south of Sydney.
snippet: It was oppressively hot, above 40 Celsius (104 Fahrenheit), and the wind was picking up. Bushfires were devastating nearby towns and now threatened Yanderra, a small village with just over 600 people located south of Sydney.
lead_paragraph: YANDERRA, Australia — It was oppressively hot, above 40 Celsius (104 Fahrenheit), and the wind was picking up. Bushfires were devastating nearby towns and now threatened Yanderra, a small village with just over 600 people located south of Sydney.
headline_main: Fight or Flight: Australians Grapple With Difficult Decision as Bushfires Approach
headline_print_headline: Fight or Flight: Australians Grapple With Difficult Decision as Bushfires Approach

abstract: Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell said on Monday that Republicans had not ruled out hearing witnesses in the impeachment trial of President Donald Trump, one of the main sticking points in drafting rules for the proceedings.
snippet: Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell said on Monday that Republicans had not ruled out hearing witnesses in the impeachment trial of President Donald Trump, one of the main sticking points in drafting rules for the proceedings.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell said on Monday that Republicans had not ruled out hearing witnesses in the impeachment trial of President Donald Trump, one of the main sticking points in drafting rules for the proceedings.
headline_main: McConnell Says Senate Republicans Have Not Ruled Out Witnesses in Trump Impeachment Trial
headline_print_headline: McConnell Says Senate Republicans Have Not Ruled Out Witnesses in Trump Impeachment Trial

abstract: The leaders of South Korea and China said Monday that they look forward to improved ties following a protracted disagreement over the deployment of a U.S. anti-missile system that Beijing considers a threat.
snippet: The leaders of South Korea and China said Monday that they look forward to improved ties following a protracted disagreement over the deployment of a U.S. anti-missile system that Beijing considers a threat.
lead_paragraph: BEIJING — The leaders of South Korea and China said Monday that they look forward to improved ties following a protracted disagreement over the deployment of a U.S. anti-missile system that Beijing considers a threat.
headline_main: China, South Korea Look to Improve Ties With Beijing Summit
headline_print_headline: China, South Korea Look to Improve Ties With Beijing Summit

abstract: Roche Holding AG made its second major gene therapy deal in a year on Monday, spending $1.15 billion to obtain the rights to Sarepta Therapeutics Inc's investigational drug to treat duchenne muscular dystrophy (DMD) outside the United States.
snippet: Roche Holding AG made its second major gene therapy deal in a year on Monday, spending $1.15 billion to obtain the rights to Sarepta Therapeutics Inc's investigational drug to treat duchenne muscular dystrophy (DMD) outside the United States.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - Roche Holding AG made its second major gene therapy deal in a year on Monday, spending $1.15 billion to obtain the rights to Sarepta Therapeutics Inc's investigational drug to treat duchenne muscular dystrophy (DMD) outside the United States.
headline_main: Roche Dives Deeper Into Gene Therapy With $1.15 Billion Sarepta Licensing Deal
headline_print_headline: Roche Dives Deeper Into Gene Therapy With $1.15 Billion Sarepta Licensing Deal
